<% title "Jobs in Computer Programming" %>
<% big_center_text "The Right Tech Job.  Now." %>

<div class="wmj_maintainance">
  WantMyJob Recommendations (this site) is being put into
  low-effort maintainance mode while new effort goes into
  <a href="http://profiles.wantmyjob.com">WantMyJob Profiles</a>.
  The site will remain up and usable, but won't be expanded
  for some time.
</div>

<h2> Get Started </h2>

  <p>
    <span class="emphatic">Answer simple questions</span>
    for us about your tech jobs.
    <span class="emphatic">We recommend jobs</span> from
    our database.
    Answer more, get better recommendations.
    <span class="emphatic">Free to use.  Always</span>.
  </p>

  <div class="cleaner_h20"></div>

  <div class="button float_l">
    <%= link_to("Start Now!", new_user_registration_path) %>
  </div>
  <div class="float_l"> &nbsp; &nbsp; or &nbsp; &nbsp; </div>
  <div class="button float_l">
    <%= link_to("Log In", new_user_session_path) %>
  </div>

  <div class="cleaner_h20"></div>

  <p class="secondary">
    Is your company hiring?  Answer questions about them and
    we'll send good matches their way, automatically.
  </p>

  <div class="cleaner_h20"></div>

  <div>
    <span class="emphatic">Some jobs we know about:</span>

    <% @jobs.each do |job| %>
      <div class="company inset">
        <span class="primary"><%= job.employer %></span>
          <span class="secondary"><%= job.title %></span>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <p></p><p></p><p></p>

  <div>
    This was a <a href="http://apps.ycombinator.com/item?id=1857136">a
    Hacker News November App</a>.  Thanks
    to Howard Yeend of <a href="http://www.weddingbudgetbuddy.com">Wedding
    Budget Buddy</a> for
    organizing a link exchange, though it never seemed to go far.
  </div>
</div>
